=== Book for children ===
* ''The Flying Cauldron'' (Літаючий казан), 2003, {{ISBN|966-7964-14-0}}

Nobel Laureate [[Mo Yan]] said in the preface of the book Ihor Pavlyuk ''"A Flight over the Black Sea"'': 
<blockquote>I know that a nebulous terrain exists in the hearts and minds of every person, a terrain that cannot be adequately characterized in simple terms of right and wrong or good and bad. I see this ambiguity in Ihor Pavlyuk’s works and I am happy in the knowledge that there is a very good poet in Ukraine.<ref>[http://www.waterloopress.co.uk/#/ihor-pavlyuk/4584096892 Ihor Pavlyuk. Flight Over the Black Sea. Selected Poems]</ref></blockquote>

